iDN42, aka Decentralized Network 42, is a large, decentralized		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iVPN-based network. But unlike other traditional VPNs, DN42 itself		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
idoesn't provide any VPN exits, which means it doesn't allow you to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ibypass Internet censorships or unlock streaming services. On the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
icontrary, the goal of DN42 is to simulate another Internet. It uses		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
imuch of the technology running on modern Internet backbones (BGP,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
irecursive DNS, etc), and is a great replica of a real network		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ienvironment.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIn short, DN42 is:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- NOT suitable for users only seeking privacy protection or bypassing		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  censorship		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- NOT suitable for users consuming large amounts of bandwidth/data,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  such as for unlocking streaming services		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- IS suitable for users learning about networking, practicing		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  configuration of servers and routers, and even preparing for an AS		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  on the real Internet		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- IS suitable for users with a real AS, but is worried of		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  [knocking out the Internet due to configuration errors](https://blog.cloudflare.com/how-verizon-and-a-bgp-optimizer-knocked-large-parts-of-the-internet-offline-today/),		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  and want a test field.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iBecause of this, the bar to enter DN42 is a bit high. Just like the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ireal Internet, you will be playing the role of a ISP, register your		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ipersonal ID, ASN, IPv4 and IPv6 blocks, and announce your IP blocks on		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iyour server with BGP. You also need to contact other users and peer		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwith them, so you can enter the "real" DN42 step by step.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iDN42 is running on `172.20.0.0/14` and `fd00::/8`, IP blocks reserved		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifor internal usage. In other words, whatever you do on DN42 won't		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iimpact real Interner connections.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
