i## Choose BGP Software		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe BGP protocol is used to exchange route information between DN42		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iusers. Here is a list of widely used, BGP supported routing software:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i1. BIRD Internet Routing Daemon **(v2)**		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - Supports various routing protocols, including BGP, OSPF, RIP, etc		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - Supports both IPv4 and IPv6		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - Clear configuration syntax yet powerful		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - ATTENTION: this is for BIRD2, which is different from BIRD1.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - BIRD configuration is a bit complicated, so please refer to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i     [DN42 Wiki's Bird2 Guide](https://wiki.dn42.us/howto/Bird2),		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i     where a copy-paste-able config is available.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i   - You can directly use BIRD's official repo in Debian:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
