i## Limit Traffic on DN42 Interfaces		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe tunnel established during a DN42 peering usually allows traffic to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iany IP (unless you set AllowedIPs for WireGuard), and this creates a		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
irisk: your peer can inject packets destined for public IPs to your		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
itunnel, and your node will forward them to the public Internet, under		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iyour name. If your peer is exploiting this for a network attack, you		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwill be in great trouble.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iTherefore, it's recommended that you set up iptables rules to block		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iforwarding from your peers to the Internet.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> Note: you don't need this if you only use WireGuard. WireGuard		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> already has IP limitations built-in.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe following rules will restrict traffic to DN42 IP ranges on all		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iinterfaces with name starting with `dn42-`:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```bash		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -N DN42_INPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_INPUT -s 172.20.0.0/14 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_INPUT -s 172.31.0.0/16 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_INPUT -s 10.0.0.0/8 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_INPUT -s 224.0.0.0/4 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_INPUT -j REJECT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A INPUT -i dn42+ -j DN42_INPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -N DN42_OUTPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d 172.20.0.0/14 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d 172.31.0.0/16 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d 10.0.0.0/8 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d 224.0.0.0/4 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A DN42_OUTPUT -j REJECT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iiptables -A OUTPUT -o dn42+ -j DN42_OUTPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -N DN42_INPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_INPUT -s fd00::/8 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_INPUT -s fe80::/10 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_INPUT -s ff00::/8 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_INPUT -j REJECT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A INPUT -i dn42+ -j DN42_INPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -N DN42_OUTPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d fd00::/8 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d fe80::/10 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_OUTPUT -d ff00::/8 -j ACCEPT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A DN42_OUTPUT -j REJECT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iip6tables -A OUTPUT -o dn42+ -j DN42_OUTPUT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
