i## BGP Session Setup: BIRD v1 & v2		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iI will only talk about the configuration of BIRD v1 and v2 since they		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iare the most widely used. I assume you have finished the setup		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifollowing the Wiki but don't have any peers.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- [DN42 Wiki's Bird2 Guide](https://wiki.dn42.us/howto/Bird2)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- [DN42 Wiki's Bird1 Guide](https://wiki.dn42.us/howto/Bird)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFor BIRD v1, what you need is:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```bash		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Add to /etc/bird/peers4/dn42_lantian.conf		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Rename dn42_lantian to whatever you want		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iprotocol bgp dn42_lantian from dnpeers {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Set to my (or your peer's) DN42 IPv4 address and ASN		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    neighbor 172.22.76.185 as 4242421234;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    direct;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i};		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Add to /etc/bird/peers4/dn42_lantian.conf		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Rename dn42_lantian to whatever you want		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iprotocol bgp dn42_lantian from dnpeers {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Set to my (or your peer's) link-local IPv6, the tunnel's interface name, and ASN		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    neighbor fe80::1234 % 'dn42-lantian' as 4242421234;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    direct;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i};		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iFor BIRD v2, what you need is:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```bash		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Add to /etc/bird/peers/dn42_lantian.conf		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Rename dn42_lantian_v4 to whatever you want		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iprotocol bgp dn42_lantian_v4 from dnpeers {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Set to my (or your peer's) DN42 IPv4 address and ASN		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    neighbor 172.22.76.185 as 4242421234;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    direct;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Disable IPv6 route exchange in IPv4 BGP, strongly recommended		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    ipv6 {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        import none;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        export none;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    };		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i};		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Rename dn42_lantian_v6 to whatever you want		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iprotocol bgp dn42_lantian_v6 from dnpeers {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Set to my (or your peer's) link-local IPv6, the tunnel's interface name, and ASN		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    neighbor fe80::1234 % 'dn42-lantian' as 4242421234;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    direct;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Disable IPv4 route exchange in IPv6 BGP		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # You may remove these statements if you want to use "multiprotocol BGP" (MP-BGP)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    ipv4 {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        import none;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        export none;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    };		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i};		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
