i- ROA, or Route Origin Authorization, checks if a route comes from the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  AS it's supposed to. For example, my `172.22.76.184/29` should come		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  from `4242422547`. Routes failing the check will be rejected;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - DN42 Wiki has a ROA configuration guide for BIRD: see		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    [Bird2](https://wiki.dn42.us/howto/Bird2) or		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    [Bird1](https://wiki.dn42.us/howto/Bird)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Community Filter, that assigns scores to links in DN42 based on		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  latency, bandwidth, and encryption, and selects a faster route based		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  on them		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - For Bird1, refer to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    [DN42 Wiki's Bird Communities Page](https://wiki.dn42.us/howto/Bird-communities).		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    For Bird2, changes are needed, and you may try out yourself		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
